    {
        "id": 6,
        "title": "Messages to Young People",
        "description": "Messages to Young People” is a collection of letters written by Ellen G. White to her children before the death of her eldest son, Henry, at the age of sixteen.\r\n\r\nThese letters reflect heartfelt parental counsel grounded in biblical principles, aimed at building strong character and spiritual commitment in youth.\r\n\r\nThe volume also includes material from the original compilation, including Uriah Smith’s address at Henry White’s funeral and selected writings from other contributors.",
        "file_path": "content/documents/6a3ec68be490b.pdf",
        "cover_image": "content/documents/covers/6a3ec68dea673.png",
